RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAPPER ZAPPER stalked near the back of the pack on the first turn, was allowed to find his stride trailing at the half mile marker, started to rally picking up horses on the rail midway on the far turn, was full of run bursting through on the fence at the furlong pole and edged away for the win crossing the wire. JIM'S HOPE travelled in mid-pack on the inside early on, settled into a good rhythm tucked in on the rail behind the engaged twosome at the half, was coaxed to keep up five sixteenths out, was gaining momentum when encouraged left handed five wide to be in range of the leaders straightening out for the drive, closed strongly late but could not get there in time. CALUSA DONNIE settled in midfield on the outside in the beginning, had a good position keeping a close touch to the front duo on the the outside at the half, was urged to go after the pair up top with three eighths to go, loomed four wide turning for home and was outfinished by rivals in the late stages. UNDER SURVEILLANCE took command on the rail entering the first turn, had a slim advantage while hounded outside down the backstretch, came under a ride relinquishing the lead with three eighths to run, resurged on the inside in the two path to regain the lead briefly at the furlong marker but could not hold off the closers in deep stretch and settled on the fringes in the end. QUIET INTENT tracked outside into the first turn, was content to just sit off the pacesetter on the outside down the back straight, began to inch away up front three furlongs from the finish, was headed on each side at the top of the stretch, dueled up top through the stretch and faded in the last sixteenth. GOODLUCKMATE hesitated on the break slightly to trail in the early going, improved a position taking closer order to the leaders along the backstretch, could not make up any ground throughout the far turn and had little to give in the stretch run.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 10 7F All Weather Track CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 111600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PARK PLACE broke sharply, sped clear, set the pace inside, drew away in the stretch when asked. LEGAL CATCH stalked from outside mid-pack, swung six wide, gained the place. ALPHA MEISTER broke a step slowly, settled at the back, went two to three wide on the turn, came out a bit for the drive, rallied between runners late exchanging minor contact but got up for show. ROYAL QUALITY was forwardly-positioned early, steadied slightly as the leader crossed in, tracked from in behind two to three wide, exchanged a light bump late, was outkicked for the placings. TOWN'S WARRIOR was forwardly-positioned stalking three to four wide on the turn, drifted out a bit in mid-stretch, was outkicked. THE NEW MAYBE was up close early, forced in a bit and ducked further clearing the gap, needed more late. ITS JUST MONEY broke a step slowly, switched out racing off the rail up the backstretch mostly two wide, kept on evenly in behind foes. DARE TO BE KING raced off the pace, went three to four wide on the turn, failed to menace. MIDNIGHT TEMPESTA settled at the rear, swung eight wide, was never near enough to threaten. PROUD RONIN went four to five wide on the turn, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, made no bid. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF ROYAL QUALITY AGAINST ALPHA MEISTER ALLEGING INTERFERENCE AS WELL AS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
